cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for multi-atlas segmentation in biomedical applications, specifically for cardiac MR images. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image segmentation. The paper also involves deep learning architecture and end-to-end training, which suggests it could also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which could also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
